</P>
<P>
   4. THE DEAD BABY MYSTERY, by Atul Gawande
</P>
<P>
   Sudden Infant Death Syndrome is not really a disease but rather
the name we've given to one of the great medical mysteries of our
time.
</P>
<P>
   1200 words. Slugged: BC-SLATE--DEAD-BABY-MYSTERY-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   (To publish any of these articles, or other articles on the
Slate site--www.slate.com--call a New York Times Syndicate sales
representatives Bob Farnell, Olivia Vasquez or Connie White at
(888) 2-NYTSYN (888-269-8796).
</P>
</TEXT>
