takes)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MARTIN (Hempstead, N.Y.) -- Curtis Martin is alive, well,
and healthy -- and playing for Bill Parcells again. How is he
adjusting to offseason surgery and new surroundings? By Michael
Holley. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-EDWARDS-SHAW (Foxborough, Mass.) -- Who will rise to the top
of the heap and be the Patriots' back of the future, or will the
Patriots employ an RB-by-committee? By Michael Madden. 1250 words.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) -- Five exhibition games
certainly helped the perception that the Patriots might be on their
way the SuperBowl. But the Patriots' play also indicated that they
need to show more. By Nick Cafardo. 1100 words.
