<P>
   &UR; Starting defense:  &LR; LE Rick Lyle; LT Jason Ferguson; RT Ernie
Logan; RE Pleasant; LLB Mo Lewis; MLB Pepper Johnson; RLB James
Farrior; LCB Aaron Glenn; RCB Otis Smith; FS Kevin Williams; SS
Victor Green.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Special teams:  &LR; K John Hall; P Nick Gallery; KR Glenn; PR Leon
Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; 4. Buffalo Bills
</P>
<P>
   Head coach:  &LR; Wade Phillips.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; 1997 record:  &LR; 6-l0.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; New faces:  &LR; QB Rob Johnson, FB Sam Gash, QB Doug Flutie, WR
Kevin Williams, G Joe Panos, LB Sam Cowart, FB Jonathan Linton.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Outlook: &LR;  Bills could be the surprise team of the division.
Depends on if Johnson (acquired from Jacksonville) is as good as
they think he can be. New offensive coaching staff and a change in
system. Bills will throw the ball more downfield. No outstanding
WRs. Couldn't run the ball well last year. Lost LB Bryce Paup and
CB Jeff Burris to free agency. Bruce Smith and Ted Washington will
