   HELICOPTER-CRASH (Washington) _ Two Air Force Blackhawk
helicopters, each with six people, have crashed in a remote area of
Nevada. By Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a' code)
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL-BRIEFING (Undated) _ The weekly column of news and
notes on politics. By B. Drummond Ayres Jr.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-COLUMN (Undated) _ The weekly Religion Column. By Peter
Steinfels.
</P>
<P>
   Plus two baseball features written for news pages:
</P>
<P>
   ND-MARIS-HOMETOWN (Fargo, N.D.) _ While most of the country is
gripped by irrepressible excitement as Mark McGwire of the St.
Louis Cardinals and Sammy Sosa of the Chicago Cubs move ever closer
to the magic number, people in Fargo are wrestling with more
complicated feelings. They are grateful for the sudden flood of
recognition being paid their cherished hero, but achingly aware it
is more of a requiem than a coronation. It's not just that Roger
Maris, who died in 1985 of lymphatic cancer, was one of their own.
It's also that people from this modest prairie town are moved by
some of the sadder particulars of the Maris story: that he felt
hounded by reporters and denigrated by those who did not want him
to break Babe Ruth's 60-run record in 1961. By Pam Belluck.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   NY-SOSA-DOMINICANS (New York) _ For America's largest community
of Dominican immigrants there's only one home run hero, and they
wonder why Sammy Sosa isn't getting the type of attention that Mark
McGuire is getting. By David W. Chen.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEW YORK &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
