</P>
<P>
   ECON-REPORT (Washington) _ The labor market rebounded in August
as GM workers returned following the strikes' settlement. The
unemployment rate was unchanged at 4.5 percent. Payrolls rose by
365,000 jobs, in line with forecasts. Workers' average hourly
earnings, a gauge of business costs, rose half a percent, or 7
cents, after having increased 0.2 percent during July. By Sylvia
Nasar.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ After opening higher, stocks have an up and
down day. At 2:05 p.m., the Dow industrial average was down 38
points, the Nasdaq down 7. Overseas, prices gained 2.3 percent in
Hong Kong and fell 1.5 percent in Tokyo. They rose 1.4 percent in
Frankfurt and 0.2 percent in London. On the American debt market,
at midday the long bond was down 8/32 point, with the yield at 5.32
percent.
</P>
