<P>
   FBN-SAINTS-HAZING _ DAYTON, Ohio _ A little less than two weeks
ago, some 30 veteran players of the New Orleans Saints shocked not
just the NFL, but a lot of folks in general when they ended their
training camp with a brutal 1 a.m. hazing incident that battered 5
rookies, including Andy McCullough, a Dayton-area prep star. Two
players ended up going to the hospital. All the players _ who had
pillowcases tied over their heads _ were severely beaten with
fists, kicks and socks that had been filled with coins. Some
rookies hid in terror and one ran to get security. The incident
finally ended when security arrived, just as a player slammed
through a third-floor window. That player made a few comments after
the incident, but has said nothing since. And all other players
until now have closed ranks and refused to discuss the matter with
NFL Security, which is investigating the matter, as well as Saints
coach Mike Ditka and team president Bill Kuharisch. (Archdeacon,
Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UT-STADIUM _ AUSTIN, Texas _ As workers rush around the
clock to get Memorial Stadium's new eastside spruced up for today's
game against New Mexico State, students came to a Thursday open
house to get a sneak preview of their new seats. Two first-year law
students are new converts, but an undergraduate student says she's
not convinced. Besides, the nose-bleed seats are making her
nauseous. We wrap up what's left to do before gameday. (Shah,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
