when I held my daughters for the first time. Tears splattered my
face, but somehow I felt as though I were in the middle of a
marvelous laugh with one _ or all five _ of my sisters. My
daughters' safe arrivals did not so much make me happy as make me
realize how splendid happiness can be. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES.
