   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-VIETNAM - Before I visited Vietnam, I took a look at the
Web site of the Vietnamese embassy in Washington. The Vietnamese
must have thought some re-education was called for when the nations
resumed diplomatic ties in 1995, because the first sentence that
popped up on my screen was this: ``Vietnam is a country, not a
war.'' Vietnam is indeed more that the sum of its battles. It is an
ancient country with a distinctive culture and a natural beauty
that runs from mountains to vast river deltas to a serpentine coast
that has more beachfront than California. (Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH LAYOUTS and PHOTOS.
</P>
