<P>
   &UR; SPORTS EDITORS, NATIONAL EDITORS, PHOTO EDITORS:  &LR; The New York
Times is planning special packages of articles as Mark McGwire and
Sammy Sosa approach and surpass the home run record. The plans are
necessarily fluid, but in tentative terms here is what you can
expect:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHEN THE COUNT REACHES 60: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE (St. Louis) _ A game story by Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SOSA (Chicago) _ A game story by Bill Dedman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE-VESCEY-COLUMN (St. Louis) _ A Sports of The Times
column on the tying of Babe Ruth's old record.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE-RUTH (undated) _ A reflection on the man who
established 60 home runs as the benchmark for measuring the
greatest hitters. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHEN THE COUNT REACHES 61:  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE (St. Louis or dateline to come) _ Game story by
Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SOSA (Chicago or dateline to come) _ Game story by Bill
Dedman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MARIS (undated) _ Robert Lipsyte recalls the final interview
Roger Maris gave before his death in 1985.
</P>
<P>
   (This story will move for Sunday publication regardless of
whether Maris' record of 61 has been tied or broken by that time.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHEN THE COUNT REACHES 62:  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE (dateline to come) _ Game story by Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic on home run history.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SOSA (dateline to come) _ Game story by Bill Dedman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE(or SOSA)-VESCEY-COLUMN (dateline to come) _ A Sports
of The Times column on the new record.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE(or SOSA)-PROFILE (dateline to come) _ Man in the
News profile on the new home run king. By Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE(or SOSA)-REACTIONS (dateline to come) _ Color and
comments from citizens in the home city of the record-breaker. This
story will move on cycle for AM publication if the record is broken
in the afternoon, or the next day as a folo if in a night game. By
Dirk Johnson.
</P>
