 &HT;    ACC FOOTBALL CAPSULES
 &HT;    Compiled by Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEMSON VS. FURMAN
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 1 p.m., Memorial Stadium, Clemson, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Clemson leads 38-10-4.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Clemson 7-4; Furman 7-4.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Furman has not scored a touchdown at Clemson
since a 35-6 loss in 1961.... Clemson has six starters back from a
defense that was 16th nationally in total defense (312.6 yards) but
is missing All-America LB Anthony Simmons, who turned pro a year
early.... For the first time in four years, the Tigers will have a
new starting quarterback, Brandon Streeter, who played well against
Florida State last year.
</P>
<P>
   WAKE FOREST VS. AIR FORCE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 1 p.m., Falcon Stadium, Colorado Springs,
Colo.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Wake Forest 5-6; Air Force 10-3.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Wake Forest is coming off its best season in six
years and is looking for more, with 16 returning starters, eight on
offense and defense.... Air Force has 17 starters back from a bowl
team whose defense allowed an average of 12.4 points a game.... The
Deacons return the high-flying passing attack of QB Brian Kuklick
and WRs Desmond Clark and Jammie Deese.... Clark's 72 receptions
set a school single-season record, and he needs just 37 more to
become the ACC career leader.
</P>
<P>
   MARYLAND VS. JAMES MADISON
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 6 p.m., Byrd Stadium, College Park, Md.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Maryland 2-9; James Madison 5-6.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Maryland has the youngest roster in Division I-A,
with 21 freshmen and sophomores among the 44 players on the
two-deep roster.... The Terrapins are seeking a better start than
coach Ron Vanderlinden's 1997 debut, a 21-14 loss to Ohio U....
Maryland LB Eric Barton is listed on the Butkus Award watch lists,
while sophomore TB LaMont Jordan is a preseason candidate for the
Doak Walker Award.... Maryland's top four wide receivers from last
year return to help new starting QB Ken Mastrole.
</P>
<P>
   NORTH CAROLINA VS. MIAMI, OHIO
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 6 p.m., Kenan Stadium, Chapel Hill, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: UNC leads 4-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: North Carolina 11-1; Miami 8-3.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: The Carl Torbush era begins, and the Tar Heels'
former defensive coordinator has to replace seven starters from the
nation's second-best overall defense last year.... After platooning
with Chris Keldorf last year, UNC QB Oscar Davenport returns as one
of the best all-around offensive threats in the ACC. He completed
62 percent of his passes for 1,380 yards and seven TDs until being
injured against Florida State.... Miami, which upset Virginia Tech
last year, was sixth in the country in scoring with 37.5 points
last year.
</P>
<P>
   DUKE VS. WESTERN CAROLINA
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m., Wallace Wade Stadium, Durham,
N.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Duke leads 1-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Duke 3-8; Western Carolina 3-8.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: A veteran Duke team has nine starters back on
defense, including All-ACC second team DT Chris Combs, and six on
the offense.... A spruced-up Wallace Wade Stadium features a new $1
million jumbo scoreboard in one end zone, repaved concourses and
freshly painted stadium seats and walls.... The Blue Devils won't
see much of it over the first part of the season, playing three of
their first five games away from home.... All of Duke's wins in
1997 came against nonconference opponents.
</P>
