<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SEC FOOTBALL CAPSULES
 &HT;    Compiled by Mark Schlabach
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   TENNESSEE VS. SYRACUSE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, noon, Carrier Dome, Syracuse, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Tennessee leads 1-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Tennessee 11-2; Syracuse 9-4.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: The game marks the starting debut of Vols
quarterback Tee Martin, who replaces NFL No. 1 pick Peyton Manning.
... Tennessee is 5-1 in openers under coach Phillip Fulmer. ...
Orangemen quarterback Donovan McNabb was Big East offensive player
of the year last season, accounting for 2,892 all-purpose yards.
</P>
<P>
   OLE MISS VS. MEMPHIS
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 12:30 p.m., Vaught-Hemingway Stadium,
Oxford, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Ole Miss leads 39-8-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Memphis 4-7; Mississippi 8-4.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Ole Miss has won seven of the last 10 meetings.
... Memphis was picked to finish sixth in Conference USA by the
league's coaches. ... Ole Miss had only four seniors listed on its
tentative depth chart _ two on offense, two on defense. ...
Quarterback Romaro Miller makes his first start for the Rebels.
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY VS. LOUISVILLE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 3 p.m., Papa John's Cardinal Stadium,
Louisville.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Kentucky leads 8-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Kentucky 5-6; Louisville 1-10.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Louisville will be breaking in its new coach,
John L. Smith, who's formerly Utah State coach, and its new
stadium. ... Kentucky quarterback Tim Couch is an early Heisman
candidate after throwing for 3,884 yards and 37 TDs last year. ...
The Wildcats have won both games in Louisville in the series.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE VS. VANDERBILT
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 6 p.m., Scott Field, Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Mississippi State leads 7-6-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Vanderbilt 3-8; Mississippi State 7-4.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game Notes: Vandy debuts its new offense, a one-back set with
a short passing game, under new coordinator Steve Crosby. ...
Commodores cornerback Jimmy Williams also is expected to play six
to 10 plays on offense. ... Sherrill has never faced Vanderbilt.
... Bulldogs tailback James Johnson rushed for 1,069 yards and 12
touchdowns in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA VS. THE CITADEL
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 6 p.m., Florida Field, Gainesville, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Florida leads 12-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: The Citadel 6-5; Florida 10-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: The schools meet for the first time since 1953.
... Under Spurrier, the Gators are 8-0 in openers and have
outscored their opponents 379-122. ... Sophomore Jesse Palmer gets
the start at quarterback for Florida, with Doug Johnson shelved
with shoulder problems.
</P>
<P>
   ALABAMA VS. BRIGHAM YOUNG
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m., Bryant-Denny Stadium, Tuscaloosa,
Ala.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Brigham Young 6-4; Alabama 4-7.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game Notes: Alabama has won its last seven openers. ...
Alabama installed new turf at Bryant-Denny Stadium just two weeks
ago. ... Tide starting QB John David Phillips has completed only
one pass in his career. ... BYU is picked to finish second in the
WAC.
</P>
<P>
   ARKANSAS VS. SOUTHWESTERN LOUISIANA
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m, Razorback Stadium, Fayetteville,
Ark.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Arkansas leads 2-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Southwestern Louisiana 1-10; Arkansas 4-7.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game Notes: Houston Nutt, former coach at Idaho, makes his
debut as Arkansas coach. ... Southwestern Louisiana allowed 553
points last season, the most allowed in a season in NCAA history.
The Ragin' Cajuns scored only 166. ... Arkansas tailback Madre Hill
returns after a two-year layoff because of knee surgery.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA VS. BALL STATE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m.; Williams-Brice Stadium, Columbia,
S.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   -- 1997 records: Ball State 5-6; South Carolina 5-6.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game Notes: South Carolina is 9-4 in non-SEC games under
Scott. ... The Gamecocks' top returning tackler, free safety Arturo
Freeman, is out for the year with a knee injury. ... Carolina
quarterback Anthony Wright returns from a knee injury that
sidelined him for the last two games of 1997.
</P>
<P>
