prospect. The club gets together on the first Wednesday of every
month to review its holdings, analyze new companies, check the
status of its ``fantasy stock game,'' and vote on new stock
purchases. This month was no different, even though the club's
portfolio got clobbered by the recent stock market swing. (Tim
Shaffer/New York Times Photo)
