and well-connected Ms. Tilberis and a handful of grass-roots
organizations, along with recent developments in diagnosis and
treatment, ovarian cancer has finally begun to make inroads into
the charitable arena dominated by more easily marketed diseases
like breast cancer and AIDS. (Librado Romero/New York Times Photo)
</P>
