<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC'S BIG MAC DELIVERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   USC special teams coach Shawn Slocum said he wasn't worried when
freshman punter Mike MacGillivray averaged less than 33 yards per
kick in the Trojans' final preseason scrimmage.
</P>
<P>
   ``Some of that scrimmage was scripted situations where he was
supposed to kick short,'' Slocum said.
</P>
<P>
   MacGillivray allayed any fears about his lack of experience
against Purdue, averaging 44.1 yards in seven kicks.
</P>
<P>
   ``The punter was outstanding. Mike MacGillivray really exceeded
my expectations,'' Slocum said. ``A 44-yard average, we'll take
that.''
</P>
<P>
   There were concerns about MacGillivray heading into the game,
but it had more to do with his finger than foot. MacGillivray
jammed a finger when it got caught in a car door, and Slocum was
worried he might have problems holding on to the ball.
</P>
<P>
   ``He got it wrapped up and didn't have any problems,'' Slocum
said.
</P>
<P>
   Slocum looked like a genius against Purdue in his first game as
special teams coach. Besides MacGillivray's impressive performance,
USC blocked a field goal, returned a kickoff for a touchdown and
converted two field goals.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, being a coach, Slocum did find some areas that need
improvement.
</P>
<P>
   ``Just the little details on things like punt pressure,'' Slocum
said. ``We have a ways to go.''
</P>
<P>
   Successful surgery: Tailback Malaefou MacKenzie underwent
surgery at USC University Hospital on Friday to repair a torn
anterior cruciate ligament in his left knee.
</P>
<P>
   MacKenzie will redshirt this season and have three years of
eligibility remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Quiet weekend: USC will take today off, hold a light practice
Sunday and take Monday off before resuming full-contact practices
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Soward to return kickoffs: USC coach Paul Hackett said wide
receiver R. Jay Soward will work his way back into returning
kickoffs against San Diego State, even though Chad Morton is
considered the No.1 kick returner.
</P>
<P>
   ``(R. Jay's) going to have to earn his spurs,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Soward, who has returned three kickoffs for touchdowns in his
career, will start at wide receiver.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
